data.name: label_polarization_ellipse_info.Text
data.value: The problem is solved using Transfer matrix method to obtain output signal of the light passing through the optical setup The optical setup contains a fixed polarizer with angle zero with respect to the x axis and a rotating quarter wave plate retarder The output signal contains a DC component representing the total intensity of the light, an AC component with twice the retarder rotation frequency and two AC components with frequency 4 times of the retarder rotation frequency. All the magnitudes of those components are calculated numerically throgh Fourier analysis
